==English==
===Etymology===
First used by John Berkenhour in 1769<br>
The name is probably his as well, a mistake for rodents apparently migrating on Danish ships.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
[[Image:Rattus norvegicus 1.jpg|thumb|right|150px|'''Rattus norvegicus''']]
# ''Rattus norvegicus'', also known as the brown rat, the wharf rat or the common rat is probably the best known of rats; it is also one of the largest. Originally from China, but now one of the world's universal [[pest]]s, eating and contaminating human and animal foodstocks, and for spreading disease.